Description:
Annotation on the envelope: "Rubens Altes Testament Judith"

- Photocopies (made in the Rubenianum) of reproductions of 'Judith and Holofernes'
- Correspondence with Karl Warns dated 27.11.1948
- Reproductions of 'Judith and Holofernes'
- Extracts from different publications
- Notes about Rubens' Judith in Collecting Point, Munich (dated 15.11.1948)
- Bibliographic references
